    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#CIG"/> <citedRange>5157 a</citedRange> (part)</bibl>, from 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#pacho1827"/>, pl. <citedRange>LXVI.1</citedRange></bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SGDI"/> <citedRange>4864</citedRange></bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#oliverioTacc"/>, <citedRange>XII.87</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>199e</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>007300</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#cassels1955"/>, p. <citedRange>34</citedRange></bibl>
                    <bibl><ptr target="#dthorn-thorn2009"/>, p. <citedRange>223</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63123"><name nymRef="#Ἄριστις">Ἄριστις</name> 
                        <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Ο_" type="patronymic"><seg part="I">Ο</seg></name><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p> Aristis fils d'O<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p> Aristis son of O<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p> Aristis figlio di O<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>أريستيس بن  أو[...؟ ..].</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>About the successive phases of the discovery and publication, see at <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr007400</ref>.</p>
	           <p>After O, Oliverio's copy had "<foreign xml:lang="it">altre lettere non chiare</foreign>". We choose to take this O as the first letter of the 
	           father's name. It might also stand for the article <foreign xml:lang="grc">ὁ</foreign>, but such a formulation is not usual in other funerary mentions 
	           inside Cyrenaican tombs.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
